Description: Buff ware pottery tray with four feet; one corner lost.
Curator's comments: Marked on base as coming from cemetery a, in rubbish, not in grave. For excavations at site see D. Randall-MacIver and A.C. Mace, El-Amrah and Abydos 1899-1901, London (1902), Similar to the tray or model bed illustrated as Decorated ware D83 in Petrie’s Corpus of Prehistoric Pottery, from Naqada tomb 1470 dated Naqada IIA.
